Hearing the tale the NereidS, too, came mounted on various beasts: one (maiden above but fish below) rides the dread sea-tiger of Tartessus 3 another is carried by that fierce ram, the terror of the Aegean, who shatters ships with his forehead3 a third bestrides the neck of a sea-lion3 another is borne along by the sea-calf to which she clings. They vie with one another in bringing gifts to the newly-wedded pair. Cymothoe presents a girdle, Galatea a precious necklace, Psamatbe a diadem heavily en- crusted with pearls gathered by herself from the depths of the Red Sea. Doto suddenly dives to gather coral, a plant so long as it is beneath the water, a jewel once it is brought forth from the waveS.
